# Rise by Solis — Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# .env.local is gitignored. NEVER commit real keys.
#
# Expo exposes EXPO_PUBLIC_* variables to the client bundle.
# Variables without EXPO_PUBLIC_ are server-side only (Expo API routes).
#
# ─── RevenueCat ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# iOS API key from RevenueCat dashboard → Projects → API Keys → Public SDK Key.
# Used by SubscriptionService to initialise Purchases on app launch.
#
# RevenueCat dashboard setup required:
#   1. Create app: "Rise by Solis" → iOS
#   2. Create product in App Store Connect: com.solis.rise.annual ($79/year)
#   3. Create entitlement: identifier must be exactly "premium_entitlement"
#   4. Create offering: attach the annual product as default package
#   5. Paste the iOS Public SDK Key below
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_API_KEY=

# ─── OpenAI / Anthropic ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Used by app/api/generate-protocol+api.ts (server-side only).
# No EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix — never exposed to the client bundle.
#
# If using OpenAI:
OPENAI_API_KEY=
#
# If using Anthropic Claude API instead:
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─── Notes ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Firebase credentials are handled via google-services.json (Android) and
# GoogleService-Info.plist (iOS). They are not environment variables.
# Add both files to the ios/ and android/ directories after eas build generates them.
# Both files are gitignored by the default Expo .gitignore.
